message.content: This question requires basic knowledge about the organs in the human body and their composition. The heart is responsible for contracting and pumping blood throughout the body, and is therefore composed mostly of muscle tissue. Option (B), the brain, is incorrect because the brain is primarily made up of neurons and glial cells, not muscle tissue. Option (C), the liver, is incorrect because the liver is primarily made up of hepatocytes, which are specialized liver cells. Option (D), the kidney, is incorrect because the kidney is primarily made up of nephrons, which are specialized structures responsible for filtering waste products from the blood.
